<div class="example-card">
<div class="example-header">
<span class="example-tag">quickstart</span>
<h3>Hello Agent</h3>
</div>
<p>A minimal workflow that answers a question with a single model call. The perfect starting point.</p>
<div class="example-code">

```yaml
workflow:
  id: hello-agent
  version: 0.1.0
  state_schema:
    query: str
    answer: str
  start: think

nodes:
  think:
    type: model
    model: claude-haiku-4-5-20251001
    prompt: "Answer: {{ state.query }}"
    output_key: answer
    next: end

  end:
    type: end
```

</div>
<div class="example-footer">
<a href="https://github.com/jamjet-labs/examples/tree/main/hello-agent">View on GitHub →</a>
</div>
</div>

<div class="example-card">
<div class="example-header">
<span class="example-tag">web search</span>
<h3>Research Agent</h3>
</div>
<p>Searches the web with Brave Search (MCP), then synthesizes a structured research report using Claude.</p>
<div class="example-code">

```yaml
nodes:
  search:
    type: tool
    server: brave-search
    tool: web_search
    arguments:
      query: "{{ state.query }}"
      count: 10
    output_key: results
    next: synthesize

  synthesize:
    type: model
    model: claude-sonnet-4-6
    prompt: |
      Results: {{ state.results }}
      Write a report on: {{ state.query }}
    output_key: report
    next: end
```

</div>
<div class="example-footer">
<a href="https://github.com/jamjet-labs/examples/tree/main/research-agent">View on GitHub →</a>
</div>
</div>

<div class="example-card">
<div class="example-header">
<span class="example-tag">multi-step</span>
<h3>Code Reviewer</h3>
</div>
<p>Reads a GitHub PR via MCP, reviews it with Claude, scores the review quality with an eval node, and posts a comment.</p>
<div class="example-code">

```yaml
nodes:
  fetch-pr:
    type: tool
    server: github
    tool: get_pull_request
    arguments:
      repo: "{{ state.repo }}"
      number: "{{ state.pr_number }}"
    output_key: pr_data
    next: review

  review:
    type: model
    model: claude-sonnet-4-6
    prompt: "Review this PR: {{ state.pr_data }}"
    output_key: review
    next: check-quality

  check-quality:
    type: eval
    scorers:
      - type: llm_judge
        rubric: "Is this a thorough, constructive code review?"
        min_score: 4
    on_fail: retry_with_feedback
    next: post-comment
```

</div>
<div class="example-footer">
<a href="https://github.com/jamjet-labs/examples/tree/main/code-reviewer">View on GitHub →</a>
</div>
</div>

<div class="example-card">
<div class="example-header">
<span class="example-tag">multi-agent</span>
<h3>Orchestrator + Specialists</h3>
</div>
<p>An orchestrator agent that delegates to specialist agents (research, writing, fact-check) using the A2A protocol.</p>
<div class="example-code">

```yaml
nodes:
  plan:
    type: model
    model: claude-sonnet-4-6
    prompt: "Break this task into subtasks: {{ state.task }}"
    output_key: plan
    next: research

  research:
    type: a2a_task
    agent_url: "{{ env.RESEARCH_AGENT_URL }}"
    input:
      query: "{{ state.plan.research_query }}"
    output_key: research
    next: write

  write:
    type: a2a_task
    agent_url: "{{ env.WRITER_AGENT_URL }}"
    input:
      topic: "{{ state.task }}"
      research: "{{ state.research }}"
    output_key: draft
    next: end
```

</div>
<div class="example-footer">
<a href="https://github.com/jamjet-labs/examples/tree/main/orchestrator">View on GitHub →</a>
</div>
</div>

<div class="example-card">
<div class="example-header">
<span class="example-tag">human-in-the-loop</span>
<h3>Approval Workflow</h3>
</div>
<p>Agent proposes an action, waits for human approval via webhook, then executes. 24-hour timeout with escalation.</p>
<div class="example-code">

```yaml
nodes:
  propose:
    type: model
    model: claude-sonnet-4-6
    prompt: "Propose a solution for: {{ state.task }}"
    output_key: proposal
    next: await-approval

  await-approval:
    type: wait
    event: human_approved
    timeout_hours: 24
    on_timeout: escalate
    next: execute

  execute:
    type: model
    model: claude-sonnet-4-6
    prompt: "Execute this approved plan: {{ state.proposal }}"
    output_key: result
    next: end
```

</div>
<div class="example-footer">
<a href="https://github.com/jamjet-labs/examples/tree/main/approval-workflow">View on GitHub →</a>
</div>
</div>

<div class="example-card">
<div class="example-header">
<span class="example-tag">python sdk</span>
<h3>Customer Support Bot</h3>
</div>
<p>A Python-native workflow that classifies support tickets, searches a knowledge base, and drafts responses.</p>
<div class="example-code">

```python
@workflow(id="support-bot", version="0.1.0")
class SupportBot:
    @node(start=True)
    async def classify(self, state: State) -> State:
        response = await self.model(
            model="claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
            prompt=f"Classify: {state['ticket']}",
            system="Output JSON: {category, priority}",
        )
        return {"classification": response.json()}

    @node
    async def search_kb(self, state: State) -> State:
        results = await self.tool(
            "knowledge-base", "search",
            {"query": state["ticket"], "category":
             state["classification"]["category"]},
        )
        return {"kb_results": results.content}

    @node
    async def draft_reply(self, state: State) -> State:
        response = await self.model(
            model="claude-sonnet-4-6",
            prompt=f"Draft a support reply using: {state['kb_results']}",
        )
        return {"reply": response.text}
```

</div>
<div class="example-footer">
<a href="https://github.com/jamjet-labs/examples/tree/main/support-bot">View on GitHub →</a>
</div>
